jthread
------------------------------------------
The JThread package provides some classes to make use of threads easy on
different platforms. The classes are actually rather simple wrappers around
existing thread implementations.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.9-1
  libgcc1-4.5.3-3
  libstdc++6-4.5.3-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.22.51-1
  cmake-2.8.4-1
  cygport-0.10.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  gcc4-g++-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://research.edm.uhasselt.be/~jori/page/index.php?n=CS.Jthread

Canonical download:
  http://research.edm.uhasselt.be/jori/jthread/jthread-1.3.1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack jthread-1.3.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./jthread-1.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/jthread-1.3.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/jthread-1.3.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libjthread1.3.1-1.3.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libjthread-devel-1.3.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(jthread)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/jthread.README
  /usr/share/doc/jthread/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/jthread/README.txt
  /usr/share/doc/jthread/TODO

(libjthread1.3.1)
  /usr/bin/cygjthread-1.3.1.dll

(libjthread-devel)
  /usr/include/jthread/jmutex.h
  /usr/include/jthread/jmutexautolock.h
  /usr/include/jthread/jthread.h
  /usr/include/jthread/jthreadconfig.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/JThread/JThreadConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/libjthread.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/jthread.pc

